    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Optical interferometry technique which involves study of the fringe pattern created when holograms capturing three dimensional information about the surface of the same object are reconstructed and superimposed.  After a stress is applied to the object, its new surface geometry is compared with a previously recorded state. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
